 270      # Helper used to test foreign messages and groups. 
 271      # 
 272      # composite_field_name should be the name of a non-repeated 
 273      # composite (i.e., foreign or group) field in TestAllTypes, 
 274      # and scalar_field_name should be the name of an integer-valued 
 275      # scalar field within that composite. 
 276      # 
 277      # I never thought I'd miss C++ macros and templates so much. :( 
 278      # This helper is semantically just: 
 279      # 
 280      #   assert proto.composite_field.scalar_field == 0 
 281      #   assert not proto.composite_field.HasField('scalar_field') 
 282      #   assert not proto.HasField('composite_field') 
 283      # 
 284      #   proto.composite_field.scalar_field = 10 
 285      #   old_composite_field = proto.composite_field 
 286      # 
 287      #   assert proto.composite_field.scalar_field == 10 
 288      #   assert proto.composite_field.HasField('scalar_field') 
 289      #   assert proto.HasField('composite_field') 
 290      # 
 291      #   proto.ClearField('composite_field') 
 292      # 
 293      #   assert not proto.composite_field.HasField('scalar_field') 
 294      #   assert not proto.HasField('composite_field') 
 295      #   assert proto.composite_field.scalar_field == 0 
 296      # 
 297      #   # Now ensure that ClearField('composite_field') disconnected 
 298      #   # the old field object from the object tree... 
 299      #   assert old_composite_field is not proto.composite_field 
 300      #   old_composite_field.scalar_field = 20 
 301      #   assert not proto.composite_field.HasField('scalar_field') 
 302      #   assert not proto.HasField('composite_field') 
 303      def TestCompositeHasBits(composite_field_name, scalar_field_name): 
 304        proto = unittest_pb2.TestAllTypes() 
 305        # First, check that we can get the scalar value, and see that it's the 
 306        # default (0), but that proto.HasField('omposite') and 
 307        # proto.composite.HasField('scalar') will still return False. 
 308        composite_field = getattr(proto, composite_field_name) 
 309        original_scalar_value = getattr(composite_field, scalar_field_name) 
 310        self.assertEqual(0, original_scalar_value) 
 311        # Assert that the composite object does not "have" the scalar. 
 312        self.assertTrue(not composite_field.HasField(scalar_field_name)) 
 313        # Assert that proto does not "have" the composite field. 
 314        self.assertTrue(not proto.HasField(composite_field_name)) 
 315   
 316        # Now set the scalar within the composite field.  Ensure that the setting 
 317        # is reflected, and that proto.HasField('composite') and 
 318        # proto.composite.HasField('scalar') now both return True. 
 319        new_val = 20 
 320        setattr(composite_field, scalar_field_name, new_val) 
 321        self.assertEqual(new_val, getattr(composite_field, scalar_field_name)) 
 322        # Hold on to a reference to the current composite_field object. 
 323        old_composite_field = composite_field 
 324        # Assert that the has methods now return true. 
 325        self.assertTrue(composite_field.HasField(scalar_field_name)) 
 326        self.assertTrue(proto.HasField(composite_field_name)) 
 327   
 328        # Now call the clear method... 
 329        proto.ClearField(composite_field_name) 
 330   
 331        # ...and ensure that the "has" bits are all back to False... 
 332        composite_field = getattr(proto, composite_field_name) 
 333        self.assertTrue(not composite_field.HasField(scalar_field_name)) 
 334        self.assertTrue(not proto.HasField(composite_field_name)) 
 335        # ...and ensure that the scalar field has returned to its default. 
 336        self.assertEqual(0, getattr(composite_field, scalar_field_name)) 
 337   
 338        self.assertTrue(old_composite_field is not composite_field) 
 339        setattr(old_composite_field, scalar_field_name, new_val) 
 340        self.assertTrue(not composite_field.HasField(scalar_field_name)) 
 341        self.assertTrue(not proto.HasField(composite_field_name)) 
 342        self.assertEqual(0, getattr(composite_field, scalar_field_name))
